citation: Proclamation under the Gas Infrastructure (Miscellaneous Amendments) Act 2002 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Gas Infrastructure (Miscellaneous Amendments) Act 2002

I, the Lieutenant-Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 2 of the Gas Infrastructure (Miscellaneous Amendments) Act 2002 fix 1 July 2003 as the day on which Parts 1 , 2 and 3 of that Act commence.

27 June 2003

W. J. E. COX

Lieutenant-Governor

By His Excellency's Command,

P. A. LENNON

Minister for Economic Development, Energy and Resources

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 30 June 2003

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Infrastructure, Energy and Resources.
